WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.259 --> 00:00:11.450
-a traditional bacon and eggs breakfast baked
right into a cornbread muffin.

00:00:11.450 --> 00:00:16.430
These bacon and egg muffins make a crowd-pleasing
brunch recipe.

00:00:16.430 --> 00:00:20.740
Being by preheating the oven to 400 degrees.

00:00:20.740 --> 00:00:26.800
Cook 4 slices of bacon that you've cut into
thirds and drain them on a paper towel lined

00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:27.800
plate.

00:00:27.800 --> 00:00:30.480
Reserve the drippings.

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:35.940
Brush 12 2-1/2 inch muffin cups with more
of the reserved bacon drippings and set them

00:00:35.940 --> 00:00:36.940
aside.

00:00:36.940 --> 00:00:47.890
Then into a small bowl, add 3 eggs, 2 tablespoons
of water, and a dash of salt and pepper.

00:00:47.890 --> 00:00:56.399
Beat this altogether and add the drippings
back to the skillet now then pour the eggs

00:00:56.399 --> 00:01:03.140
into the hot skillet over medium heat and
cook, but don't stir until the eggs begin

00:01:03.140 --> 00:01:07.770
to set on the bottom and around the edges.

00:01:07.770 --> 00:01:13.180
Lift and fold the eggs with a large spatula
so the uncooked eggs flow under the cooked

00:01:13.180 --> 00:01:17.280
one.

00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:21.650
Continue cooking the eggs until they're set,
but still moist.

00:01:21.650 --> 00:01:25.320
Remove them to a bowl and set them aside.

00:01:25.320 --> 00:01:33.280
In a medium bowl, add 1 cup of all-purpose
flour, a half cup of yellow corn meal, 2 tablespoons

00:01:33.280 --> 00:01:41.110
of sugar, 2-1/2 teaspoons of baking powder,
and a half teaspoon of salt.

00:01:41.110 --> 00:01:44.380
Stir all of this together.

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:52.909
Then in a separate bowl with 2 more eggs,
add 1 cup of milk and a quarter cup of vegetable

00:01:52.909 --> 00:01:56.210
oil or melted butter.

00:01:56.210 --> 00:02:00.070
Use a whisk to blend this together.

00:02:00.070 --> 00:02:07.210
Stir this mixture into the dry ingredients.

00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:08.800
Fold the scrambled eggs.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:17.319
Add a half cup of shredded cheddar cheese
into the muffin batter.

00:02:17.319 --> 00:02:20.709
Spoon the batter into the muffin cups.

00:02:20.709 --> 00:02:28.420
Lastly, top each muffin cup with 1 piece of
the bacon.

00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:34.120
Bake the muffins for 15 to 17 minutes or until
they're light brown And toothpick inserted

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:38.620
into the center comes out clean.

00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:44.989
Set the muffin tin on a wire rack and let
the muffins cool in the pan for 5 minutes

00:02:44.989 --> 00:02:50.749
then run a small table knife or metal spatula
around the inside edges of the cups to loosen

00:02:50.749 --> 00:02:53.239
the muffins from the pan.

00:02:53.239 --> 00:02:59.590
Remove the muffins from the pan and serve
them warm with a little drizzle of maple syrup

00:02:59.590 --> 00:03:01.519
if you like.

00:03:01.519 --> 00:03:05.099
Bacon and eggs and sweet morning muffins all
in one.

00:03:05.099 --> 00:03:06.139
How can you top that?

